---
description: general files management for each new file
alwaysApply: true
---

# most important

each platform has its owned folder at project root. for example: 
  - running a nicegui platform, it has a new folder, such as `/ui_nicegui` etc. 
  - design a llm function, using llama_ccp. the new folder could be `/llm_llamacpp`
  - desing a llm platform that's for intel cpu only. The new folder could be `/llm_opennovi`


# less important

use the default platform folder structure in its own folder, except user has his special consideration

all testing files are in the `/test` folder; build a folder for platforms if using. for example:
  - pytest serial files are in the `/test/pytest`.
  - gradio test files are in the `/test/gradio`.
  - general tests but called mcp could put in the `test/mcp_general/`

all plan files are in the `/docs` folder. if the plan has a couple of files, build a folder in the `/docs`

spec-kit build up files are in the `/plans` folder. Each plan has it owned sub-folder in the `/plans`

